    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "In 1991, I think it was, when I returned to Bergen-Belsen, I couldn't believe how flat the place was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "But I knew approximately where I slept, where this tent barrack must have been, because [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It was close to the crematorium, which also burned day and night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Would-- would you mind if I go back to Auschwitz just for a moment?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I failed to say that, through the terrible smell, I eventually lost my sense of smell in Auschwitz-Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I'd like to say more about that in a second.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
